1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION congratulating the Trinity
2 Lutheran High School girls volleyball team.
3 Whereas, The Trinity Lutheran High School girls volleyball
4 team captured their second consecutive IHSAA Class 1A state
5 championship on November 8, 2025;
6 Whereas, Despite graduating five of six starters from the
7 2024 season when the Trinity Lutheran Cougars captured their
8 first state championship, they returned to the title match in
9 2025 and beat Faith Christian in four sets, 25-11, 25-15, 20-25,
10 and 25-16;
11 Whereas, Trinity Lutheran defeated Faith Christian in the
12 2024 state finals;
13 Whereas, Head Coach Janet VanLiew attributes their
20262411
HR 1547/DI 140 2026

2
1 resounding victory to the athletes' hard work, dedication, and
2 belief in their system;
3 Whereas, Senior Bailey Bonde was announced as the
4 recipient of the Mental Attitude Award by the IHSAA Executive
5 Committee. The Mental Attitude Award is annually presented
6 to a senior nominated by her principal and coach, and has
7 demonstrated excellence in mental attitude, scholarship,
8 leadership, and athletic ability during her four years of high
9 school; and
10 Whereas, The Cougars are proud to capture Trinity
11 Lutheran High School's second state title: Therefore,
12 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
13 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
14 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
15 congratulates the Trinity Lutheran High School girls volleyball
16 team on their second consecutive IHSAA state title.
17 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
18 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to State
19 Representative Jim Lucas for distribution.
